特朗普称，他目前没有任何症状，但可能“很快会接受检测”。
Trump says he has no symptoms at the moment, but could be "tested soon."
在一片对疫情应对措施的质疑声甚至愤怒声中，美国总统特朗普于东部时间周五（3月13日）下午宣布全国进入紧急状态，此举将授权他使用国会拨出的500亿美元联邦资金来应对新冠危机。
Amid skepticism and even anger over the response to the outbreak, US President Trump declared a state of emergency on Friday afternoon (March 13), a move that would authorize him to use $50 billion of federal funds allocated by Congress to address the new crown crisis.
截至特朗普召开新闻发布会时，美国已经至少有1645例新冠肺炎感染者被确诊，死亡人数41人，疫情已经蔓延至全美47个州。
By the time of Trump's press conference, at least 1,645 new cases of pneumonia had been diagnosed in the United States, killing 41 people, and the epidemic had spread to 47 states across the country.
3月11日，世界卫生组织宣布，新冠疫情经评估定性为“全球大流行”。
On March 11, the World Health Organization announced that the new crown epidemic has been assessed as a "global pandemic."
同日，美国的确诊案例超过1000例，美股应声熔断。
On the same day, the United States confirmed more than 1,000 cases, the United States shares in the meltdown.
当晚，特朗普发表全国讲话，宣布自周五起，对欧洲申根国家实施为期30天的旅行禁令。
That evening, Trump delivered a national address announcing a 30-day travel ban for European Schengen countries, starting Friday.
与此同时，美国好莱坞影星汤姆·汉克斯及夫人在澳大利亚确诊感染新冠病毒、NBA球季中止。
Meanwhile, Hollywood star Tom Hanks and his wife were diagnosed with the new crown virus in Australia and the NBA season was suspended.
同时，美国的邻国加拿大总理特鲁多的夫人确认感染新冠，一系列震撼性消息迅速席卷了全球舆论。
Meanwhile, the wife of Canada's neighboring Canadian Prime Minister Narendra Trudeau confirmed the new crown, and a series of shocking news quickly engulfed global public opinion.
美国亚利桑那州立大学公共卫生学院助理教授蕾拉·巴拉扎告诉《中国新闻周刊》，国家紧急状态的宣布可以允许疫情应对中绕开某些法律规定并使用额外资源。
Rilla Barazza, an assistant professor at the Arizona State University School of Public Health, told China News Weekly that the declaration of a state of emergency would allow for the circumvention of certain legal requirements and the use of additional resources in dealing with the epidemic.
例如，通过此次紧急状态宣布，美国授权卫生和公共服务部部长在必要时可以豁免医疗保险和医疗补助的某些要求。
For example, through this state of emergency, the United States has authorized the Secretary of Health and Human Services to waive certain Medicare and Medicaid requirements if necessary.
多位专家认为，此举是特朗普转向积极防疫的标志。
Many experts see the move as a sign of Trump's shift to aggressive immunization.
加州大学洛杉矶分校公共卫生学院副院长、流行病学资深终身教授张作风接受《中国新闻周刊》采访时指出，早在3月11日，就有人猜测总统会宣布国家紧急状态，因为美国病例数量上升较快，特朗普受到了多方压力。
As early as March 11, there was speculation that the president would declare a state of emergency because of the rapid rise in the number of cases in the United States and the pressure on Trump, Zhang style, vice president of UCLA School of Public Health and senior professor of epidemiology, told China News Weekly.
检测能力是目前美国疫情应对中饱受批评的环节。
Detection ability is a critical link in the current American epidemic response.
据美国疾控中心的数据，相比韩国每天检测1万人的数据，美国的检测数据目前甚至还未达到1.5万人。
Compared with the 10,000 people tested a day in South Korea, the number of people tested in the United States is not even 15,000, according to the CDC.
众议院议长南希·佩洛西在讨论稍晚将会通过的紧急支出方案时，就表示，“这个法案最重要的三个部分是检测、检测、检测。
"The three most important parts of the bill are testing, testing and testing," House Speaker Nancy Pelosi said as she discussed an emergency spending package to be passed later.
”此外，这笔钱还将用于免除所有学生在政府机构贷款的利息，并将购买大量原油作为美国战略储备等。
In addition, the money will be used to waive interest on loans to government agencies for all students and to buy large quantities of crude oil as US strategic reserves.
为提高检测能力，美国政府正在与谷歌合作开发一个网站，在网站上人们填写筛查问卷以确定个人是否需要进行检测，此举旨在避免生病但不一定需要新冠病毒检测的人群涌向医疗机构，而需要检测的人将依据导航，就近在沃尔玛、美国第二大零售商场”目标百货”和最大的连锁药店”沃尔格林”和CVS等商店的停车场检测中心进行取样。
To improve detection capabilities, the U.S. government is working with Google to develop a Web site where people fill out screening questionnaires to determine whether individuals need to be tested -- a move aimed at avoiding a flood of sick people who do not necessarily need a new crown virus test to health-care facilities.
上述四家连锁商业机构的CEO在新闻发布会时就站在特朗普身边。
The CEOs of the four business chains stood beside Trump at the press conference.
与此同时，政府批准罗氏公司向美国实验室出售其3.5小时即能出结果的检测试剂，并表示将向另外两家公司拨款100多万美元，以加速开发用时只需一个小时的检测试剂。
Meanwhile, the government has authorized Roche to sell its 3.5-hour ready-to-use reagent to U.S. laboratories, and has said it will allocate more than $1 million to two other companies to speed up the development of a one-hour test reagent.
特朗普说，预计下周初将增加50万次检测，下周整体的检测能力将提升至140万次，一个月内实现500万次检测。
Trump says an additional 500,000 tests are expected early next week, and overall testing capacity will increase to 1.4 million next week, with five million tests in a month.
同时，特朗普还赋予了美国卫生和公共服务部部长亚历克斯·阿扎尔一系列新的权力，比如，他可给医生和医院更大的灵活性来应对新冠疫情，包括让远程治疗变得更容易，放弃对床位数量和住院时间的严格限制、以及某些医院医生增加人数的规等等。
Trump, meanwhile, has given the US Secretary of Health and Human Services, Alex Azar, a new set of powers, for example, to give doctors and hospitals greater flexibility to deal with a new crown epidemic, including making telemedicine easier, abandoning strict limits on the number of beds and the length of hospitalization, and increasing the number of doctors in some hospitals.
“平时美国有很多规矩，处在紧急状态下，就能打破很多制约来对新冠病毒进行干预。
"There are many rules in the United States that, in a state of emergency, can break many of the constraints to intervening in the new crown virus.
”张作风说。
'said Zhang style.
2009年，为应对H1N1猪流感大流行，美国前总统奥巴马宣布全国进入紧急状态，这个一年后失效的紧急状态允许绕开一些条例——例如，允许医院在场外筛查或治疗传染病。
In 2009, in response to the H1N1 swine flu pandemic, former US President Barack Obama declared a national state of emergency, a state of emergency that expired a year later, allowing, for example, hospitals to screen for or treat infectious diseases off-site.
在组织架构上，张作风说，宣布紧急状态后，联邦紧急事务管理局能够向州和地方有序的提供系统救灾资金，组建医疗救助小组，设定流动医院等。
Organizationally, Zhang said that after the declaration of the state of emergency, the Federal Emergency Management Agency was able to provide systematic relief funds to states and localities in an orderly manner, set up medical assistance teams, set up mobile hospitals, etc.
同时联邦紧急事务管理局在全美十个大区储存药品、医疗器具、食品等物资，随时可以用于救灾。
At the same time, the Federal Emergency Management Agency stores medicines, medical devices, food and other items in 10 regions of the United States that are readily available for disaster relief.
特朗普也在发布会上敦促各个州立刻成立紧急指挥中心，并要求各医院激活应急预案。
Trump also urged states to set up emergency command centers immediately, and urged hospitals to activate emergency plans.
美国亚利桑那州立大学公共卫生学院助理教授蕾拉·巴拉扎表示，这一宣布表明总统意识到控制病毒传播的必要性，并且正在利用他的权力来采取措施实现这一点。
Rilla Barazza, assistant professor of public health at Arizona State University, said the announcement showed the president was aware of the need to control the spread of the virus and was using his power to take steps to do so.
此外，特朗普是否感染了新冠肺炎也成为万众瞩目的焦点。
Moreover, the question of whether Trump has contracted pneumonia is also in the limelight.
5天前他曾接触过的巴西总统一名助理刚刚确诊新冠肺炎。
An aide to the Brazilian president he contacted five days ago has just confirmed pneumonia.
在记者会上被问及是否应该自我隔离时，特朗普回答说不需要。
Asked at a press conference whether he should isolate himself, Trump replied that he did not need to.
确诊的巴西官员上周末到访特朗普的私人住所海湖庄园，还与特朗普、副总统彭斯合照。
Confirmed Brazilian officials visited Trump's private residence, Haihu Park, over the weekend, and took a group photo with Trump and Vice President Burns.
特朗普称，他只是跟那位巴西官员短暂合照，他目前没有任何症状，因而没有接受病毒测试。
Trump said he had taken only a brief photo with the Brazilian official, who did not have any symptoms and therefore did not undergo a viral test.
但随后他又称，可能“很快会接受检测”。
But then he added that it could be "tested soon."
图片来源：CBS电视新闻值班编辑：庄梦蕾推荐阅读▼日本“慢半拍”的疫情防控“围猎者”高乃则：曾为陕西首富，市长刚上任他就送了50万当贺礼疯狂的野味市场：疫情期间顶风作案，打科研旗号盗猎。
He's the richest man in Shaanxi province. He gave half a million dollars as a gift to the newly rich man in Shaanxi. He gave half a million dollars to the game market during the epidemic, working under the banner of scientific research.
